fake_sheet.title: Change
fake_sheet.content: In fall the leaves @change@ from green to brown.%秋天，樹葉由綠變成褐色。%更衣[（+out of/into）]%He @changed@ into a new suit.%他換上一套新的西裝。%換車 In New York, you'll @change@ for Boston.%你在紐約換車去波士頓。%def 換檔[（+up/down/into/to）]%n.變化；變更；變遷[C][U][（+of/in）]%Many @changes@ have taken place since then.%自那以來，發生了許多變化。改變一下[S1]% I think a @change@ might do you good.%我想換換環境也許對你有好處。%def 更換；替換[C][（+in/of）]%零錢；找零[U]%Here's your @change@, said thesaleswoman.%這是你的找零，女店員說道。 %def【口】絕經（期）；更年期[the S]%片語 %change of pace 改變活動%Tom studied for three hours and then read a comic book for a @change of pace@.%湯姆唸書唸了三個小時，為了調劑一下，找來一本漫畫書翻翻。%change down 放慢車速%You must @change down@ now.%你現在必須放慢車速。 %change into %把……變成 They are@changing@ desert @into@ farmland.%他們正在使沙漠變為農田。%變成%Sometimes commonnouns@change into@ proper nouns.%有時普通名詞會轉變成專有名詞。%換（衣）%You should @change into@ your working clothes before you start to do the job.%開始工作以前你應該換上工作服。%change for%轉車到……去%Where shall we @change for@ Shanghai?%我們在什麼地方轉車去上海？%change hands %易手 %That house has @changed hands@ several times in the last few months. %那所房子最近幾個月內已轉手好幾次。%change off 輪流 John and Bob @changed off@ at driving the car.%約翰和鮑伯輪流開車。 %change over %改變 %The plant @changed over@ to the manufacture of storage batteries last year.% 這家工廠去年已改產蓄電池。 %對換 %Perhaps you and I had better @change over@; you are much more experienced than I in this field.%也許我們的工作還是對換一下好；在這方面你比我更有經驗。% change up %加快車速 %I will @change@ the car @up@ now.%我現在要加快車速了。%for a change %為了改變一下 %Let's go to a movie @for a change@. %我們換個口味，去看場電影吧！ %Let's eat Italian food @for a change@. %讓我們換個口味，吃義大利菜吧！ %衍生 n. changer a. changeful %同義% vi. & vt.改變；交換；變化；變更 alter, vary,deviate, substitute, replace, modify, convert, shift, switch,transfer, turn, exchange, transform n.零錢 cash, money,coins%反義 vi. & vt.（使）改變 settle, fix n.變化，變更 niformity, monotony 同義參見%words novelty, move, adjust, interchange, innovate, orrection, convert, veer,variety, amend, adaptation, transplant, translation,transition, evolution, adapt, revolution, revision,revise, relief, reform, qualification, differentiate,development
